===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*(t)s(j)aŋ||clear; pure; clean}}; cognate with {{cog|bo|གཙང||clean; pure}}, {{cog|lus|thiang||to be clear; to be clean; to be pure}}, {{cog|qxs||ɕó}}, {{cog|duu|cangma|'''cang'''ma|clean}}, {{cog|my|စင်|t=clean, pure}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; STEDT).

Within Chinese, cognate with {{och-l|淨|clean}}, {{och-l|醒|to wake up; to become sober}}, and allofamic with {{och-l|星|star}}, {{och-l|晴|''(of weather)'' clear; fine}}; possibly also related to {{och-l|靜|quiet}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Perhaps an {{w|Mainland Southeast Asia linguistic area|areal}} word; compare {{cog|mkh-pro|*caŋ||to glitter}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

